<br>
A company making tin cans needs to ensure that they take reasonable steps to prevent those tin cans causing harm, such as providing safe opening devices, using the correct non toxic material and solder etc.   <br>
<br>
Microsoft also needs to ensure that its service is relatively safe and if they can't ensure that then they leave themselves open to possible retaliatory action by consumers who get burned.  They can't feasibly provide the moderation so they shut it down.  Makes sense to me.<br>
